    "narrative": "The Ghost Ride the WHIP lineup is heavily leveraged toward the favorable matchup against Weiss today, propelling **Mickey Moniak** (75.98) and **Tyler Soderstrom** (72.71) into our top-tier start category. **Mickey Moniak** benefits from an elite +19% SP skill boost against a struggling starter, while **Tyler Soderstrom** leverages a +10% park factor and dynamic platoon advantage to drive significant scoring potential. **Vinnie Pasquantino** (72.92) is our most consistent anchor, elevated by a strong +11% SP skill rating and a prime spot in the three-hole, making him the safest high-floor play of the day.\n\nWe are hunting stolen base efficiency in this 5x5 Roto environment, which makes **Brice Turang** (65.73) a critical start; his +4% bump due to the pitcher\u2019s slow delivery speed significantly increases his viability for a swipe. Conversely, **Jose Caballero** (67.22) earns a spot start due to a massive +13% platoon edge against Suter. The toughest bench decision involved **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (58.46), who sits just outside the \"Strong\" start threshold; despite the stolen base upside, the -7% platoon penalty against Suter kept him on the pine in favor of the higher-projected **Giancarlo Stanton** (60.17), whose presence in the heart of the order provides a more reliable RBI floor. While **James Wood** (53.91) remains a marginal play due to the pitcher's efficiency at holding runners, his lead-off role keeps him in the mix. Monitor lineup confirmation for **Luis Campusano** and **Kyle Karros**, as their deep-order spots make them the most volatile pieces of our current construction.",
